Package: scHeatmap
Title: Simple Heatmaps for Single-Cell Seurat Objects
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("scHeatmap", "Developers", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "maintainer@example.com")
Description: Provides a small, opinionated interface for creating publication-ready
    single-cell expression heatmaps from 'Seurat' objects. Cells can be split and
    ordered by metadata, genes can be arranged into marker groups, and the result
    is returned as a 'ComplexHeatmap' object for further customization.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    circlize,
    ComplexHeatmap,
    grDevices,
    grid,
    Matrix,
    RColorBrewer,
    SeuratObject
Suggests:
    Seurat,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
